               <msContents>
                  <summary> This late 14th-century <title>Kulliyāt</title> (Collected Works) of
                     Jalayirid-era panegyric poet Salmān Sāvajī (d. 1376) contains not only the
                     author's <title>Dīvān</title>, but also his <title key="work_8419">Jamshīd and
                        Khurshīd</title>, and <title>Dah'nāmah</title> (Ten Tales). Completed by
                     scribe <persName key="person_f7833" role="scr">‘Aṭā' Allāh ibn Shaykh ‘Alī</persName> in
                        <placeName cert="high" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000235"
                        key="place_7000235">Greater Iran</placeName>, possibly <placeName
                        cert="medium" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7002148"
                        >Shiraz</placeName>, in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" from="1396"
                        to="1397-10-01">799 AH (1396–97 CE)</date>, just twenty years after the
                     author's death. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_76-item1">
                     <author key="person_36059765" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/36059765/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Salmān Sāvajī, d.
                           1376</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">سلمان ساوجى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="scr" key="person_f7833">
                        <persName role="scr">‘Aṭā' Allāh ibn Shaykh ‘Alī</persName>
                     </editor>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20032" change="#ids-cleanup"
                        >Kulliyāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20032" change="#ids-cleanup">کلیات</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmalla"><locus from="1b" to="1b">برگ ۱پ (Folio
                           1b):</locus> هر دل که در هوای جمالش مجال یافت * عنقای همتش دو جهان زیر
                        بال یافت. </incipit>
                     <explicit><locus from="71b" to="71b">برگ ۷۱پ (Folio 71b):</locus> بدسم حضرت
                        سلطان عهد شیخ او پیش که عهد سلطنتش باد بتصل بر دام شد این ربیع معانی جمادی
                        الثانی سنه ثلاث و ستین ر سبع مایة تمام و الله اعلم بالصواب. </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="287a" to="287a">برگ ۲۸۷ر (Folio 287a):</locus> تمت الدیوان
                        الصاحب الاعظم افتخار و املح الشعر العالم حسان الزمان سحبان البیان جمال الملة
                        و الدین خواجه سلمان علیه الرحمة و الغفران علی ید العبد المحتاج الی فضل الله
                        ابن الشیخ علي عطا الله فی یوم الاحد حادی عشرین سعبان المعظم سنه تسع و تسعین
                        و سبعمایه. </colophon>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="313a" to="313a">برگ ۳۱۳ر (Folio
                           313a):</locus> همیشه روزگار پادشاه اسلام فرخ همایون باد و از نوایب و
                        مصایب مصون و محروس بمحمد و آله الطاهرین. </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="313a" to="313a">برگ ۳۱۳ر (Folio 313a):</locus> تمت کتاب حدایق
                        السحر فی علم الشعر علی ید العبد المحتاج الی فضل الله ابن الشیخ علي عطا الله
                        اصلح الله شانه اللهم اغفر لکاتبه و لصاحبه و لقاریه و لمن نطرفیه امن برب
                        العالمین. </colophon>
                     <colophon>Two colophons, one on <locus from="287a" to="287a">287a</locus> dated
                           <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1397-05-28">Sunday 21 Sha‘bān 799 AH
                           (28 May 1397 CE)</date>, and another on folio <locus from="313a"
                              to="313a">313a</locus> signed by the scribe <persName  key="person_f7833" role="scr">‘Aṭā'
                           Allāh ibn Shaykh ‘Alī</persName>. </colophon>
                     <note>In his addendum on <locus from="ib" to="ib">first right flyleaf b side
                           (f. ib)</locus>, former owner <persName role="ato ins fmo"
                           ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/44733962/" key="person_44733962">Sir Gore
                           Ouseley</persName> misinterprets the date of completion of the work by
                        the author given in the explicit on <locus from="71b" to="71b">71b</locus>,
                           <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1362-06-23">Sunday 21 Sha‘bān 763 AH
                           (23 Jun. 1362 CE)</date>, as a date of completion of that portion of the
                        manuscript, then repeated by <persName role="cataloguer"
                           ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/3970228/" key="person_3970228">Michael
                           Kerney</persName> in his handlist. For a copy of this poet's
                           <title>Dīvān</title>, see Rylands <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7027"><idno>Persian
                              MS 531</idno></ref>.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <!-- add msItems for the different works
                     -->

                  </msItem>
